org.apache.ctakes.ytex.kernel

Class ImputedFeatureEvaluatorImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ctakes.ytex.kernel.ImputedFeatureEvaluatorImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ImputedFeatureEvaluator

    public class ImputedFeatureEvaluatorImpl
extends Object
implements ImputedFeatureEvaluator
    Calculate the mutual information of each concept of a corpus wrt a concept graph and classification task (label) and possibly a fold. We calculate the following:
    • raw mutual information of each concept (infogain). We calculate the joint distribution of concepts (X) and document classes (Y), and compute the mutual information for each concept.
    • mutual information inherited by parents (infogain-parent). For each concept in the concept graph, we merge the joint distribution of child concepts. This is done recursively.
    • mutual information inherited by children from parents (infogain-child). We take the top n concepts and assign their children (entire subgraph) the mutual info of the parent.

    The mutual information of each concept is stored in the feature_rank table. The related records in the feature_eval table have the following values:

    • type = infogain, infogain-parent, infogain-imputed, infogain-imputed-filt
    • feature_set_name = conceptSetName
    • param1 = conceptGraphName
    How this works in broad strokes:
    • evaluateCorpus(Parameters) load instances, iterate through labels
    • evaluateCorpusLabel(Parameters, ConceptGraph, InstanceData, String) load concept - set[document] map for the specified label, iterate through folds
    • evaluateCorpusFold(Parameters, Map, ConceptGraph, InstanceData, String, Map, int) create raw joint distribution of each concept, compute parent joint distributions, assign children mutual info of parents
    • completeJointDistroForFold(Map, Map, Set, Set, String) computes raw joint distribution of each concept
    • propagateJointDistribution(Map, Parameters, String, int, ConceptGraph, Map) recursively compute parent joint distribution by merging joint distro of children.
    • #storeChildConcepts(Parameters, String, int, ConceptGraph) take top ranked parent concepts, assign concepts in subtrees the mutual info of parents. Only concepts that exist in the corpus are added (depends on computing the infocontent of concepts with CorpusEvaluator)
    Author:
    vijay
